headlines.description: Miami's perfect season is over. The Hurricanes can only hope their shot at a spot in the College Football Playoff isn't gone too.
headlines.shortLinkText: Freshman Pickett leads Pitt to 24-14 upset over No. 2 Miami

video.headline: Pitt forces fumble to take down Miami

events.name: Baylor Bears at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: Kenny Hill threw touchdowns to three different receivers and ran 3 yards for another score as No. 10 TCU clinched a spot in the Big 12 championship game with a 45-22 win over Baylor on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 10 TCU gets Big 12 title shot with 45-22 win over Baylor

video.headline: TCU tops Baylor, punches ticket to Big 12 title game

events.name: South Florida Bulls at UCF Knights

headlines.description: Mike Hughes' 95-yard kickoff return with 1:28 remaining was the difference as No. 12 Central Florida completed the first unbeaten regular season in program history with a wild 49-42 victory over No. 19 South Florida on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: No. 12 UCF caps perfect regular season with win over USF

video.headline: UCF beats South Florida in thriller to remain unbeaten

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Josh Jackson threw a touchdown pass and No. 24 Virginia Tech beat Virginia for the 14th consecutive time, 10-0 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson's 19th TD pass, Hokies 'D' stops Virginia, 10-0

events.name: Western Michigan Broncos at Toledo Rockets

headlines.description: Logan Woodside threw for 300 yards and two touchdowns, and Toledo beat Western Michigan 37-10 on Friday to secure a spot in the Mid-American Conference championship game.
headlines.shortLinkText: Toledo beats Western Michigan to claim MAC's West Division

video.headline: Woodside connects with McKinley-Lewis for Toledo TD

tracking.trackingName: NCF_Final Game Highlight Toledo (Woodside connects with McKinley-Lewis for Toledo TD) 2017/11/24

headlines.description: D'Eriq King threw for 277 yards and a touchdown and ran for two more scores to lead Houston to a 24-14 win over Navy on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: King accounts for 3 TDs, leads Houston past Navy, 24-14

video.headline: Houston hands Navy second straight loss

events.name: Northern Illinois Huskies at Central Michigan Chippewas

headlines.description: Shane Morris threw his third touchdown pass on a daring fourth down play with 1:32 to play, Josh Cox intercepted a pass at the goal line with 22 seconds left and Central Michigan beat Northern Illinois 31-24 on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Central Michigan rallies past N Illinois 31-24 behind Morris

headlines.description: Tyree Jackson threw a pair of touchdown passes and Khalil Hodge had an interception in the end zone with 1:20 left to help Buffalo seal a 31-24 victory over Ohio on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hodge's INT in end zone helps Buffalo hold off Ohio 31-24

video.headline: Hodge INT saves game for Buffalo

tracking.trackingName: NCF_Final Game Highlight (Hodge INT saves game for Buffalo) 2017/11/24

headlines.description: Tucker McCann made a 19-yard field goal with five seconds remaining, and Missouri extended its winning streak to six straight games with a 48-45 victory over Arkansas on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lock, Witter help Missouri earn late win over Arkansas

events.name: New Mexico Lobos at San Diego State Aztecs

headlines.description: Snubbed earlier in the week by the Doak Walker Award selection committee, Rashaad Penny ran 22 times for 203 yards and two touchdowns in his final regular-season game to crack the 2,000-yard mark and lead San Diego State to a 35-10 victory against New...
headlines.shortLinkText: SDSU's Penny gains 203 yards,  cracks 2,000-yard mark in win

headlines.description: Akrum Wadley ran for 159 yards and three touchdowns and Iowa scored 28 points in less than a 7-minute span over the halves on its way to a 56-14 win over Nebraska on Friday in what could have been coach Mike Riley's last game with the Cornhuskers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wadley, Fant help Iowa dominate Nebraska in 56-14 win

events.name: Texas State Bobcats at Troy Trojans

headlines.description: Brandon Silvers threw for 380 yards and four touchdowns and Troy rolled to a 62-9 win over Texas State on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Silvers throws 4 TD passes, Troy swamps Texas State 62-9

video.headline: Troy's Barker somersaults into the end zone for TD

events.name: Western Kentucky Hilltoppers at Florida Intl Golden Panthers

headlines.description: D'Vonte Price returned a fumbled fake punt 38 yards for a TD during a surge of 28 unanswered points that shot FIU past Western Kentucky 41-17 Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: FIU scores 28 unanswered points to defeat W. Kentucky 41-17

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Texas Longhorns

headlines.description: Nik Shimonek came off the bench in the fourth quarter to throw two touchdown passes, and Texas Tech rallied to beat Texas 27-23 Friday night and earn a victory that could save coach Kliff Kingsbury's job.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shimonek rallies Texas Tech past Texas 27-23

events.name: California Golden Bears at UCLA Bruins

headlines.description: J.J. Molson hit a 37-yard field goal with four seconds left after backup quarterback Devon Modster led a clutch scoring drive, and UCLA secured bowl eligibility under interim coach Jedd Fisch with a 30-27 victory over California on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UCLA edges Cal 30-27, gets bowl eligible under interim coach

video.headline: Rosen leaves early as UCLA edges Cal
